Most of what applies to body slam is also true of gremlin toss, though the upgrade is generally worse, and temp hp counting is a very nice bonus, since that helps gremlin toss to have better consistency in it's damage. The other big difference is that you have shield gremlins passive (as well as all the card spam stuff/wards/bubble barrier that gremlins get). Body slam tends to be fairly bad in the early game for most ironclad decks, and only really starts to shine later on in the run once you have a stronger block engine up and running, or more generically strong block cards like impervious, power through, and second wind. Gremlin toss has a smoother experience throughout the run, especially if you are focusing on shield gremlin or have extra ways to get them in front. 

It's a great finisher type card in a very defensive deck, and can be one of your only attacks if you really hone in on spamming temp hp with edible armor, herckle, or other sources (do be careful if defect is buffing neow, as the buffer can really hurt that strategy). It can also just be played as a efficient source of damage in a deck focusing on bubble barrier or other efficient block cards. Can be a bit at odds with flip out, since that already converts your block into damage, but some decks might run both if they are block heavy and need ways to frontload. I think that gremlins are good enough at blocking overall that you could take this with little to no support and expect it to perform reasonably well over a run, but you probably want to have at least some synergies first. Dexterity (oddly smooth stone, kunai) in particular can be really powerful in combination with cards that generate multiple wards (glimmer, counter strike). The other thing is that since gremlins generally need to include a strong defensive package to cover their low health, you will usually be able to support gremlin toss fairly naturally. Gets better once you know you have the 4th energy. Bad against all the act 1 elites.

Great with runic pyramid of course. Upgrade is pretty good, basically a +6 in efficiency, since you get 3 temp hp and 3 damage. It should probably receive a nerf, since it synergizes so well with gremlins defensive packages, and unlike body slam, it doesn't need anything like barricade to increase it's consistency. I could see this at rare, or maybe as a 2 cost that upgrades down to a 1 cost. I do like the gimmick of gremlin toss counting temp hp as well as block, but it makes it very powerful and consistent. Similar to how body slam was too good on guardian as an uncommon, I think that gremlin toss is too good on gremlins as an uncommon.
